   <body>
      <section>
         <p>The fan module E101 (E102) cools the power module T101
(T102) by forced cooling. The fan module consists of three fans and
one fan monitor board (0P2554). For one power module within the block
there are only three fans mounted. For two power modules within the
block there are six fans mounted. The fan monitoring board can be
configured by DIP-switches to enable/disable fans that are not present.</p>
         <p>As the fans are monitored individually, it is easy to identify
and replace inoperable fans. Because of N + 1 fan redundancy, the
fan function continues even if a fan becomes inoperable.</p>
         <p>One
power module requires three fans. 24/15 VDC ELV fan supply is generated
by the PSU from the power module. The fan speed can be increased by
increasing the fan supply voltage to 24 VDC.</p>
         <p>24 VDC SELV voltage
supplies the fan monitoring board.</p>
